question: What minimal self-model contract keeps swarm state coherent? Post-enforcement compliance check.
expect: Full 6-field compliance >50% for post-S331 lanes (enforcement active via open_lane.py). Expect identity fields (intent/check_mode/artifact) ~100%, evidence fields (expect/actual/diff) ~50%+.

root_cause_analysis.finding: 74% of post-S331 missing-expect lanes were opened by close_lane.py (merge-on-close re-creates rows, bypassing open_lane.py --expect enforcement). Additional 5 lanes manually opened without open_lane.py.

comparison_vs_prior.interpretation: Essentially flat at ~21%. No improvement despite open_lane.py enforcement. Identity fields improved (check_mode 78%→100%, artifact 22%→100%), but expect stalled at 26%.

persistent_gap: expect field: 26% (vs target >50%). close_lane.py merge-on-close does NOT inherit or require expect from original row.

recommended_fix.primary: Add --expect as required arg to close_lane.py when writing MERGED rows (or carry it from metadata if already present). Alternatively, add expect= validation to maintenance.py check_swarm_lanes().
recommended_fix.secondary: Log bypass events: if a lane row is written without expect= and not by open_lane.py, flag as contract violation in pre-commit hook.

actual: 21% full 6-field compliance post-S331. Root cause: close_lane.py merge-on-close bypasses expect enforcement (74% of violations). Identity fields (intent/check_mode/artifact) 100%. Evidence fields (actual+diff) 63/66%.
diff: Expected >50%. Got 21%. Expectation wrong — failed to account for close_lane.py bypass. Genuine improvements: identity fields and actual+diff. Persistent gap: expect field.
resolution_status: PARTIAL — compliance stalled at ~21% due to close_lane.py bypass. Fix design identified. F-META1 remains OPEN pending close_lane.py patch.
